<h1>Why is a good nutrition important?</h1>
<p>Unhealthy eating contributes to widespread obesity in the United States. Even for people at a healthy weight, bad nutrition can lead to heart disease, high blood pressure, diabetes, osteoporosis, and certain types of cancer.</p>
<p>Encouraging children to be mindful of their eating habits can carry on into adulthood and they are more likely to maintain a healthy diet in the future.</p>
<p>A balanced diet should include fruits, vegetables, whole grains, low fat dairy products, lean meats and healthy fats.</p>
